Demi Lovato was rushed to the hospital for Heroin overdose, TMZ reports. According to the report, law enforcement sources of the Los Angeles Police state that the unconscious 25-year-old was administered Narcan, an emergency drug for “narcotic overdose”. The Los Angeles police say that they received a call around 11:40 am but could not confirm her identity. This is coming after she released a song titled Sober which contrary to its name, showed that she had relapsed. The 25-year-old had been away from drugs and alcohol for six years. Before this incident, the Grammy-nominated singer was billed to perform at Atlantic City this week. PEOPLE, on the other hand, write that she has regained consciousness and state that their sources say that it was not heroin. Her famous friends have since poured speedy recovery wishes    